@apaszke
This code you wrote in THD looks very dodgy:
static THDStorage* THDStorage_(_alloc)() {
  THDStorage* new_storage = new THDStorage();
  std::memset(reinterpret_cast<void*>(new_storage), 0, sizeof(new_storage));

Do you know what's going on here? I dutifully did a placement new on the std::atomic refcount after the memset, but I'd much rather... not.

